# SqlTxt.Parser

SQL-like command parsing. Returns strongly typed command objects.

## Phase 1 SQL Subset

- `CREATE DATABASE <name>;`
- `CREATE TABLE <name> (...);`
- `INSERT INTO <table> (...) VALUES (...);`
- `SELECT <columns|*> FROM <table> [WHERE <column> = <literal>];`
- `UPDATE <table> SET <column> = <literal>[, ...] [WHERE <column> = <literal>];`
- `DELETE FROM <table> [WHERE <column> = <literal>];`

## Parsing Assumptions

- Case-insensitive keywords
- Identifiers case-preserving, normalized internally
- String literals single-quoted
- Equality-only predicates in Phase 1

## Guidelines

- Separate tokenizer and parser.
- Return command DTOs from `ICommandParser`.
- Report errors with line/column when possible via `ParseException`.
- No comments required in Phase 1.
